docs.lead_paragraph: PRINCETON, N.J., Oct. 21. -- Commemoration exercises of the one hundred and fifty-third anniversary of the founding of Princeton University were held in Alexander Hall to-day. The Faculty and Trustees had assembled in the Chancellor Greene Library and then formed a procession and marched to Alexander Hall, headed by President Patton and Mr. Whitelaw Reid.

headline.main: MR. REID ON EXPANSION; Defense at Princeton of the Government's Philippine Policy. CITES NATIONAL PRECEDENTS Military Control He Regards as Necessary for a Time, Then an Autonomous Administration.

docs.abstract: Speech on Expansion at the Commemoration Exercises of the One Hundred and Fifty-third Anniversary of the Founding of Princeton University
